    <header>
        <h1><marquee behavior="alternate";bgcolor="yellow";height="1000" >Egg Bhurji</marquee></h1>
    </header>

    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>4 eggs</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1 onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>2 tomatoes, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 green chili, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon turmeric powder</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon red chili powder (adjust to taste)</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon garam masala</li>
            <li>Salt, to taste</li>
            <li>Fresh cilantro for garnish</li>
            <li>Toast or roti for serving</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>eggs</li>
            <li>indian</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Procedure</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Crack the eggs into a bowl and beat them lightly with a fork or whisk. Set aside.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a pan over medium heat. Add chopped onions and sauté until they become translucent.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and chopped green chili. Sauté for an additional 1-2 minutes until the raw smell disappears.</li>
            <li>Stir in the chopped tomatoes and cook until they become soft and the oil starts to separate.</li>
            <li>Add turmeric powder, red chili powder, garam masala, and salt. Mix well to combine the spices with the tomatoes.</li>
            <li>Pour the beaten eggs into the pan and continuously stir until the eggs are cooked and well mixed with the tomato and spice mixture. This should result in a scrambled egg consistency.</li>
            <li>Garnish with fresh cilantro and serve the Egg Bhurji hot with toast or roti.</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious Egg Bhurji!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>


